      "description": "Called $I_1(x)$ in the paper. 2-loop 3-point master integral for $q\\bar{q}\\to VV$ planar topologies from Gehrmann, Tancredi, Weihs (1306.6344). Triangle topology with doubled edge $[1,2]$ (4 propagators, one squared indicated by dot). Two on-shell legs $p_1^2=p_2^2=0$ combined into $p_{12}=p_1+p_2$, two off-shell legs $q_1^2=q_2^2=Q^2$. Single variable $x$. Prefactor $P_1(x)=x/(m^2(1-x^2))$. Fitted at $\\varepsilon^{-1}$ (weight 2, 17 functions) and $\\varepsilon^0$ (weight 3, 58 functions). AMFlow: 8.5 CPU-min/point, 58 points, 28 digits.",
